> We can now pass such values in the first argument list of an overloaded application

It seems it works for all argument lists. The following code compile:

``` scala
def f(n: Int)(x: Int, f: Int => Int) = f(x)
def f(n: Int)(x: String, f: String => String) = f(x)

def g(m: Int)(n: Int)(x: Int, f: Int => Int) = f(x)
def g(m: Int)(n: Int)(x: String, f: String => String) = f(x)

f(4)("abc", _.reverse)
f(10)(2, _ + 2)

g(3)(4)("abc", _.reverse)
g(5)(10)(2, _ + 2)
```
